message:
Fix duplicate useState import in WarStoriesMap

The file had two separate React imports:
  import { useState } from "react";           (line 3)
  import { useEffect, useState as useReactState } from "react"; (line 11)

The second import aliased useState as useReactState to avoid a
name collision, but this was unnecessary since both imports come
from the same module. Consolidated into a single import statement:
  import { useState, useEffect } from "react";

Updated the Portal component's useState call from useReactState()
back to useState() to match.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>

